     To move in a 3D/Area/Overland mode with a mouse, click the mouse cursor
     at the edge of the display window in the direction you want to move.  To
     move forward, click at the top of the window.  To turn around, click at
     the bottom.  To turn right or left, click at the appropriate side.

     To use the mouse for combat targetting and movement, click the mouse
     cursor over the target square and the cursor will advance towards the
     target.  If the target is off the screen, first select an intermediate
     square near the edge of the screen.  To move in combat, click on the
     adjacent square you want to enter.

     Joystick movement is similar to using the cursor controls/keypad.  Select
     the Move command and then move the joystick.


